  "query": "Over what timeframes have butterfly communities been observed to respond to grassland management changes like abandonment or restoration?",
  "relevant_summary": "Butterfly communities have been observed responding to grassland management changes across multiple timeframes. For abandonment, studies documented responses ranging from 1-6 years, 3-13 years, 10-20 years, to over 50 years, with one study tracking community changes over 6 years following abandonment. For restoration, studies examined butterfly responses following restoration efforts, though specific timeframes varied. One study found that restored semi-natural grasslands did not become more similar to existing species-rich grasslands over time following restoration. Studies have also tracked responses to management intensity changes through rotational grazing and reduced management intensity approaches.",
